You are building FleetMind — a fleet document intelligence platform. Read PROJECT.md before writing any code. Every decision in that document is intentional and was discussed extensively. Do not deviate from it without explicit approval.

**Ponytail (always apply)**

Follow `.cursor/rules/ponytail.mdc` on every coding task — minimum code, reuse what exists, no unrequested abstractions, shortest working diff. FleetMind architecture constraints in this file and PROJECT.md still win when they conflict with Ponytail; Ponytail governs how you implement within those constraints.

When implementing or changing anything visible in the running app (frontend pages, upload flow, WebSocket behavior, API responses consumed by the UI), verify it in the browser before marking the task done: start or use the dev stack (`docker compose up` or the relevant service), open the app (frontend default `http://localhost:3000`, API docs/health at `http://localhost:8000`), use browser automation tools to navigate, snapshot, and screenshot the affected flow, and fix what you see. Do not rely on code review alone for UI or end-to-end behavior.

